				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-f57df6b elementor-widget elementor-widget-appluxe_faq" data-id="f57df6b" data-element_type="widget" data-e-type="widget" data-widget_type="appluxe_faq.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
					<script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is Agentic AI?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Agentic AI refers to AI systems capable of autonomously pursuing goals across multiple steps. Unlike a chatbot that responds to a single prompt, an agentic system plans, uses tools, calls APIs, and iterates until a complex objective is achieved — without constant human input."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How is Agentic AI different from traditional AI?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Traditional AI is reactive — one input, one output. Agentic AI is proactive — it breaks goals into sub-tasks, selects tools, monitors outcomes, and self-corrects. It operates with persistent memory and long-horizon planning, like a human employee working on a multi-day project."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why is Human-in-the-Loop (HITL) important?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"HITL ensures high-stakes decisions — financial transactions, customer communications, legal documents — are reviewed by humans before execution. This maintains compliance, reduces costly errors, and builds the trust required for organisation-wide AI adoption."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can Agentic AI work without any manual input?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes — for well-defined, low-risk tasks like data processing, report generation, and scheduling. For higher-risk operations, configurable approval gates are recommended so you control the level of autonomy."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Will Agentic AI replace human workers?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No — it augments. Agentic AI handles repetitive, rule-based tasks so humans focus on strategy, creativity, and relationships. The most successful deployments position AI as a force-multiplier, not a replacement."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I get started with Agentic AI?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Start small: identify one high-volume workflow, choose an API-first tool from the AppLuxe marketplace, set approval rules, and run a 30-day pilot. Measure impact, then expand systematically."}}]}</script>        <div class="alhp-sec alhp-faq" style="--ac:#ff3b3b;">
            <div class="alhp-wrap">
                <div class="alhp-sec-head">
                    <h2 class="alhp-sec-h2">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                    <p class="alhp-sec-sub">Everything you need to know about Agentic AI and autonomous business operations.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="alhp-faq-list">
                                            <div class="alhp-faq-item is-open" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <button class="alhp-faq-q" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="alfaq0" itemprop="name">
                                <span>What is Agentic AI?</span>
                                <span class="alhp-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></span>
                            </button>
                            <div class="alhp-faq-a" id="alfaq0" role="region" aria-hidden="false" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                <div class="alhp-faq-ai" itemprop="text"><p>Agentic AI refers to AI systems capable of autonomously pursuing goals across multiple steps. Unlike a chatbot that responds to a single prompt, an agentic system plans, uses tools, calls APIs, and iterates until a complex objective is achieved — without constant human input.</p></div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                                            <div class="alhp-faq-item" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <button class="alhp-faq-q" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="alfaq1" itemprop="name">
                                <span>How is Agentic AI different from traditional AI?</span>
                                <span class="alhp-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></span>
                            </button>
                            <div class="alhp-faq-a" id="alfaq1" role="region" aria-hidden="true" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                <div class="alhp-faq-ai" itemprop="text"><p>Traditional AI is reactive — one input, one output. Agentic AI is proactive — it breaks goals into sub-tasks, selects tools, monitors outcomes, and self-corrects. It operates with persistent memory and long-horizon planning, like a human employee working on a multi-day project.</p></div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                                            <div class="alhp-faq-item" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <button class="alhp-faq-q" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="alfaq2" itemprop="name">
                                <span>Why is Human-in-the-Loop (HITL) important?</span>
                                <span class="alhp-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></span>
                            </button>
                            <div class="alhp-faq-a" id="alfaq2" role="region" aria-hidden="true" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                <div class="alhp-faq-ai" itemprop="text"><p>HITL ensures high-stakes decisions — financial transactions, customer communications, legal documents — are reviewed by humans before execution. This maintains compliance, reduces costly errors, and builds the trust required for organisation-wide AI adoption.</p></div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                                            <div class="alhp-faq-item" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <button class="alhp-faq-q" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="alfaq3" itemprop="name">
                                <span>Can Agentic AI work without any manual input?</span>
                                <span class="alhp-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></span>
                            </button>
                            <div class="alhp-faq-a" id="alfaq3" role="region" aria-hidden="true" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                <div class="alhp-faq-ai" itemprop="text"><p>Yes — for well-defined, low-risk tasks like data processing, report generation, and scheduling. For higher-risk operations, configurable approval gates are recommended so you control the level of autonomy.</p></div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                                            <div class="alhp-faq-item" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <button class="alhp-faq-q" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="alfaq4" itemprop="name">
                                <span>Will Agentic AI replace human workers?</span>
                                <span class="alhp-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></span>
                            </button>
                            <div class="alhp-faq-a" id="alfaq4" role="region" aria-hidden="true" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                <div class="alhp-faq-ai" itemprop="text"><p>No — it augments. Agentic AI handles repetitive, rule-based tasks so humans focus on strategy, creativity, and relationships. The most successful deployments position AI as a force-multiplier, not a replacement.</p></div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                                            <div class="alhp-faq-item" itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                            <button class="alhp-faq-q" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="alfaq5" itemprop="name">
                                <span>How do I get started with Agentic AI?</span>
                                <span class="alhp-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></span>
                            </button>
                            <div class="alhp-faq-a" id="alfaq5" role="region" aria-hidden="true" itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                                <div class="alhp-faq-ai" itemprop="text"><p>Start small: identify one high-volume workflow, choose an API-first tool from the AppLuxe marketplace, set approval rules, and run a 30-day pilot. Measure impact, then expand systematically.</p></div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                                    </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        				</div>
				</div>
